In this thesis convolutional neural networks (CNNs) are heavily used to extract information from images. 

Due to the recent success of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for object detection, general visual object detections systems, which can detect never seen objects of various types, with reasonable accuracy and performance are now available. This enables the search for objects of given types, which is done in this work. Another CNN is used to classify the room type of areas of the environment  

Most of the research on this topic focuses on the search of a specific known object. In this thesis objects of a given type are searched. The recent progress in general object detection lead to visual object detection systems based on convolutional neural network (CNNs), which have a sufficient performance and accuracy to make this feasible. 


